# Project Rules — Bit Link

## Stack

- Next.js 16 (App Router), TypeScript strict, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui
- Drizzle ORM + Postgres, ioredis, TanStack Query v5, Zod, Recharts
- **tRPC v11** (superjson) — type-safe API layer replacing Route Handlers
- Vercel deployment, Square Cloud for Postgres + Redis

## Critical Next.js 16 Conventions

- `proxy.ts` = Node.js interceptor (auth only, `/admin/:path*`)
- `[slug]/route.ts` = Node.js route handler for slug resolution + redirect — **NOT migrated to tRPC**
- No `middleware.ts` in this project — redirect does not run on Edge
- `"use cache"` directive — **not used** in this project (analytics queries flush a Redis buffer instead)
- `params` in pages and route handlers are async — always `await params`
- `after()` from `next/server` for fire-and-forget background tasks (replaces `waitUntil`)

## tRPC Rules

- All admin API procedures go through `adminProcedure` (auth + rate limit)
- Mutations on links require `adminMutationProcedure` (includes CSRF middleware)
- Public procedures (`auth.login`) use `publicProcedure` with explicit rate limiting
- **Export endpoint** (`analytics.export`): returns JSON, not CSV (LGPD compliance — no bulk personal data download)
- tRPC routers live in `src/server/routers/` — one file per domain
- Zod schemas from `src/lib/validators/` are reused as procedure inputs
- Server Components use `createSSRCaller()` from `src/lib/trpc/server.ts` for data fetching
- Client components use `api.xxx.useQuery()` / `useMutation()` from `src/lib/trpc/react.ts`
- The `TRPCProvider` wraps the app via `QueryProvider` in the admin layout
- `[slug]/route.ts` remains a route handler — it's an HTTP redirect, not an API

## Code Conventions

- No `any`. No `as unknown as T`. TypeScript strict is not negotiable.
- All API inputs validated with Zod — shared schemas in `src/lib/validators/`
- Use `env.X` from `@/env` — never `process.env.X` directly
- Path aliases: `@/lib`, `@/components`, `@/db`, `@/env`, `@/server`
- Server-only modules must have `import 'server-only'` at the top

## Component Rules

- Default to Server Components. Add `"use client"` only when you need browser APIs, event handlers, or tRPC hooks.
- shadcn primitives live in `src/components/ui/` — do not modify them directly
- Business-logic components live in `src/components/{domain}/`

## Service & Repository Rules

- All business logic lives in **services** (`src/lib/services/`) — never in routers or route handlers
- Services lançam `DomainError` (de `src/lib/errors/`) — nunca `TRPCError`
- Repositories (`src/lib/repositories/`) encapsulam acesso a dados via Drizzle
- Repositories são classes com constructor DI (`db: DB`) — permitem mocks sem `mock.module()`
- Services dependem de interfaces (`ILinkRepository`) — não de classes concretas
- Singletons são exportados para produção, construtores para testes

## Error Handling Rules

- `DomainError` é a base de todos os erros de domínio
- `errorMapper` middleware no tRPC converte `DomainError` → `TRPCError` automaticamente
- Response helpers (`SuccessResponse`, `ErrorResponse` de `src/lib/response/`) são para REST route handlers apenas
- Use `new SuccessResponse(data)` e `new ErrorResponse({ code, message })` em route handlers

## Database Rules

- All Drizzle queries live in **repositories** (`src/lib/repositories/`) — not inline in route handlers
- Every mutable query must have a `.where()` clause
- Schema changes require: `bunx drizzle-kit generate` + `bunx drizzle-kit migrate`
- Cascade deletes defined at schema level, not application level

## Pagination Rules

- All list endpoints: cursor-based, `{ data: T[], nextCursor: string | null }`
- Cursor: `btoa(JSON.stringify({ createdAt, id }))`
- Client: `api.links.list.useInfiniteQuery` — tRPC handles TanStack Query integration
- No offset pagination anywhere in the codebase

## Analytics Rules

- `trackClick()` always via `after()` — never awaited
- `trackClick()` writes to Redis pipeline (LPUSH + LTRIM), not directly to Postgres
- `flushClickBuffer()` batch-inserts from Redis to Postgres before analytics queries
- Errors in `trackClick` and `flushClickBuffer` are swallowed silently
- Never store raw User-Agent — only `sha256hex(ua)`
- Referrer: store full URL, display `new URL(referrer).hostname`

## Auth Rules

- Login rate-limited: 5 req/min per IP (inside `auth.login` procedure)
- Admin API rate-limited: 60 req/min per IP (via `adminProcedure` middleware)
- POST/PATCH/DELETE on links require CSRF validation (via `adminMutationProcedure` middleware)
- Logout uses Server Action (`logoutAction`), not a tRPC procedure

## Git Rules

- Branch prefixes: `feature/` (human), `fix/` (bug fixes)
- All PRs target `main`
- Commit messages: `type(scope): description` — e.g. `feat(links): add expiry date field`
- No WIP commits on PRs — squash before requesting review
